President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate four individuals to the Broadcasting Board of Governors. The nominees are Walter Isaacson, Michael Lynton, Susan McCue, and Michael P. Meehan. Walter Isaacson is the President of the Aspen Institute and former Chairman and CEO of CNN. Michael Lynton is the Chairman and CEO of Sony Pictures Entertainment. Susan McCue is the President of Message Global and former Chief of Staff to Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid. Michael P. Meehan is the President of Blue Line Strategic Communications and Senior Vice President at Virilion. These nominations are part of the President's effort to promote freedom and democracy around the world.